This is the last bug for Inheritance margin on my sticky note.

Currently InheritanceMarginService has some problem with implementing/implemented symbols,
For example:
```
interface IBar
{
     void Foo();
}

class Bar : IBar
{
    public virtual void Foo() { }
}

class Bar2 : Bar
{
    public override void Foo();
}
```
For IBar.Foo, it only shows Bar.Foo in the margin.
Also for Bar.Foo, it only shows Bar.Foo in the margin

This PR fixes this.

